The paper discusses a probabilistic semi-supervised learning model that takes into account multiple annotators, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper focuses on the development of a model that can estimate the true label and annotator variable expertise for both labeled and unlabeled data. This problem is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
